Attentive to the world around me I always have a personal project underway to further my knowledge or acquire new ones.

I am currently in my third year of study and am looking for an internship as teacher-documentary specialist.
thoughtList: Whether the photograph is understood as a naïve objet or the work of an experienced artificer, its meaning–and the vierwer's response–depends on how the picture is identified or misidentified; that is, on words.  ―Susan SONTAG

Few people ask from books what books can give us. Most commonly we come to books with blurred and divided minds, asking of fiction that it shall be true, of poetry that it shall be false, of biography that it shall be flattering, of history that it shall enforce our own prejudices. If we could banish all such preconceptions when we read, that would be an admirable beginning.”― Virginia Woolf
